1
00:00:10,761 --> 00:00:13,055
Well, there we go, universal roaming.

2
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:17,100
Never have to worry
about a signal again.

3
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:20,145
No way. This is too mad.

4
00:00:20,229 --> 00:00:23,857
You're telling me I can phone anyone
anywhere in space and time on my mobile?

5
00:00:23,941 --> 00:00:28,779
As long as you know the area code.
Frequent flyers' privilege.

6
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,281
Go on, try it.

7
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:35,035
(ALARM BLARING)

8
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:39,039
Distress signal. Clocking off.
Might be a bit of...

9
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:45,629
turbulence. Sorry.
Come on, Martha, let's take a look.

10
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,507
COMPUTER:
Automated distress signal transmitted.

11
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,925
Now, that is hot.

12
00:00:50,008 --> 00:00:52,386
COMPUTER:
Automated distress signal transmitted.

13
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:54,555
It's like a sauna in here.

14
00:00:54,638 --> 00:00:59,268
Venting systems working at full pelt,
trying to cool down

15
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:04,147
wherever it is we are.
Well, if you can't stand the heat...

16
00:01:07,818 --> 00:01:10,070
-That's better.
-SCANNELL: Oi, you two!

17
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:12,823
-Get out of there!
-Seal that door now!

18
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:16,994
Who are you?
What are you doing on my ship?

19
00:01:17,578 --> 00:01:19,746
-Are you police?
-Why would we be police?

20
00:01:19,830 --> 00:01:21,081
We got your distress signal.

21
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:22,874
If this is a ship,
why can't I hear any engines?

22
00:01:22,958 --> 00:01:24,293
It went dead four minutes ago.

23
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:26,753
So maybe we should stop chatting
and get to Engineering, Captain.

24
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:27,921
(ALARM BLARING)

25
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,923
COMPUTER: Secure closure active.

26
00:01:30,007 --> 00:01:31,925
-What?
-The ship's gone mad.

27
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:37,514
Who activated secure closure?
I nearly got locked into area 27.

28
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:44,438
-Who are you?
-He's the Doctor and I'm Martha. Hello.

29
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:48,525
COMPUTER: Impact projection,
42 minutes, 27 seconds.

30
00:01:48,609 --> 00:01:51,278
We'll get out of this, I promise.

31
00:01:51,361 --> 00:01:53,488
-Doctor.
-Forty two minutes until what?

32
00:01:53,572 --> 00:01:55,365
Doctor!

33
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,535
Look!

34
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:02,998
KATH: Forty two minutes
until we crash into the sun.

35
00:03:08,397 --> 00:03:10,607
-How many crew members on board?
-Seven, including us.

36
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:12,693
We transfer cargo across the galaxy.
Everything's automated.

37
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:14,695
-We just keep the ship...
-Call the others. I'll get you out!

38
00:03:14,778 --> 00:03:16,405
-What's he doing?
-Doctor, don't!

39
00:03:20,826 --> 00:03:23,745
-But my ship's in there!
-In the vent chamber?

40
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:27,499
-It's our lifeboat.
-It's lava.

41
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:31,628
Temperature's going mad in there.
Up 3,000 degrees in 10 seconds

42
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,755
-and still rising.
-Channelling the air.

43
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:36,383
The closer we get to the sun,
the hotter that room's gonna get.

44
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:39,219
-We're stuck here.
-So we fix the engines.

45
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:42,305
We steer the ship away from the sun.
Simple. Engineering down here, is it?

46
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:45,434
-Yes.
-COMPUTER: Impact in 40:26.

47
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:49,521
Blimey. Do you always
leave things in such a mess?

48
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:52,149
-Oh, my God.
-The hell happened?

49
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:55,193
Oh, it's wrecked.

50
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:58,363
Pretty efficiently, too.
Someone knew what they were doing.

51
00:03:58,447 --> 00:04:01,324
Where's Korwin?
Has anyone heard from him or Ashton?

52
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:02,492
No.

53
00:04:02,617 --> 00:04:04,661
MARTHA: Do you mean
someone did this on purpose?

54
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:06,621
Korwin, Ashton, where are you?

55
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:10,917
Korwin, can you answer?

56
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:13,545
Where the hell is he?
He should be up here.

57
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:16,840
Oh, we're in the Toragy system. Lovely.

58
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:20,927
You're a long way from home,
Martha, half a universe away.

59
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:22,262
Yeah, feels it.

60
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:27,684
And you're still using energy scoops for
fusion. Hasn't that been outlawed yet?

61
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:32,606
We're due to upgrade next docking.
Scan all engine reports.

62
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:38,195
(BEEPING)

63
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:41,364
-No response.
-What?

64
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:47,078
They're burnt out.
The controls are wrecked.

65
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:48,497
I can't get them back online.

66
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:52,542
Oh, come on, auxiliary engines.
Every craft's got auxiliaries.

67
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,127
KATH: We don't have access from here.

68
00:04:54,211 --> 00:04:56,296
The auxiliary controls
are in the front of the ship.

69
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:59,299
There are 29 password-sealed doors
between us and them.

70
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:02,135
-You'll never get there on time.
-Can't you override the doors?

71
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:06,056
No, sealed closure means what it says.
They're all deadlock sealed.

72
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,058
So a sonic screwdriver's no use.

73
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:10,936
Nothing's any use. We've got no engines,
no time and no chance.

74
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:14,356
Oh, listen to you!
Defeated before you even started.

75
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:17,442
Where's your Dunkirk spirit?
Who's got the door passwords?

76
00:05:17,526 --> 00:05:19,736
They're randomly generated.
Reckon I'd know most of them.

77
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,279
Sorry. Riley Vashtee.

78
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:23,198
Then what are you waiting for,
Riley Vashtee? Get on it.

79
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:24,950
Well, it's a two-person job.

80
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:27,035
One to take this for the questions.

81
00:05:27,118 --> 00:05:29,120
The other to carry this.

82
00:05:29,204 --> 00:05:32,123
The oldest and cheapest security system
around, eh, Captain?

83
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,292
Reliable and simple.
Just like you, eh, Riley?

84
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:38,713
-Try to be helpful, get abuse. Nice.
-I'll help you. Make myself useful.

85
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:40,507
It's remotely controlled
by the computer panel.

86
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:44,511
-That's why it needs two.
-Oi, be careful.

87
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,389
You, too.

88
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,933
(OVER PA) McDonnell, it's Ashton.

89
00:05:50,225 --> 00:05:53,895
-Where are you? Is Korwin with you?
-Get up to the med centre now.

90
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:06,658
COMPUTER: Impact in 34:31.

91
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:10,787
-I've got to stop it!
-Korwin, it's Abi.

92
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:13,999
Open your eyes.
I need to take a look at you.

93
00:06:14,124 --> 00:06:15,917
Korwin! What's happened? Is he okay?

94
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:18,962
Help! Help me! It's burning me!

95
00:06:19,588 --> 00:06:22,757
-How long's he been like this?
-Ashton just brought him in.

96
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,843
-What are you doing to him?
-Don't get too close.

97
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:28,972
-Don't be stupid. He's my husband.
-And he's just sabotaged our ship.

98
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:31,391
-What?
-He went mad.

99
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:33,268
He put the ship under secure closure.

100
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,228
Then he sent a heat pulse
to melt the control.

101
00:06:35,312 --> 00:06:37,981
-No way! He wouldn't do that.
-I saw it happen, Captain.

102
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,233
Korwin?
Korwin, open your eyes for me a second.

103
00:06:40,317 --> 00:06:42,527
-I can't.
-Yeah, of course you can. Go on.

104
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,738
Don't make me look at you. Please.

105
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:48,491
All right, all right,
all right, just relax. Sedative.

106
00:06:52,913 --> 00:06:54,539
What's wrong with him?

107
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:57,500
Rising body temperature,
unusual energy readings.

108
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:00,712
Stasis chamber.
I do love a good stasis chamber.

109
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:03,506
Keep him sedated in there.
Regulate the body temperature.

110
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:07,469
And just for fun, run a bio-scan,
a tissue profile and a metabolic detail.

111
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,095
Just doing them now.

112
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:11,973
Oh, you're good.
Anyone else presenting these symptoms?

113
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,893
-Not so far.
-Well, that's something.

114
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:16,645
Will someone tell me
what is the matter with him?

115
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:19,064
Some sort of infection.
We'll know more after the test results.

116
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:24,027
Now, allons-y! Back downstairs, eh?
See about those engines. Go.

117
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,613
Hey! Go.

118
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:32,410
Call us if there's news. Any questions?

119
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:36,706
-Yeah. Who are you?
-I'm the Doctor.

120
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:49,052
COMPUTER: Heat shield failing at 25%.

121
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:52,305
Impact in 32:50.

122
00:07:54,224 --> 00:07:58,311
-Hurry up, will you?
-All right. Fix the clamp on.

123
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:02,107
What are you typing?

124
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:05,902
These doors' trip code is the answer
to a random question set by the crew.

125
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:08,822
Nine tours back,
we got drunk, thought them up.

126
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:12,617
Reckoning was, if we're hijacked, we're
the only ones who know all the answers.

127
00:08:12,701 --> 00:08:16,955
-So you type in the right answer...
-This sends a remote pulse to the clamp.

128
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:22,043
But we only get one chance per door.
Get it wrong, the whole system freezes.

129
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,421
-Better not get it wrong, then.
-Okay.

130
00:08:24,671 --> 00:08:28,925
"Date of SS Pentallian's first flight?"
That's all right. Go!

131
00:08:31,136 --> 00:08:33,930
-Yes!
-Twenty eight more to go!

132
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:35,515
(MARTHA LAUGHING)

133
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:38,893
Abi, how's Korwin doing?
Any results from the bio-scan?

134
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:40,770
He's under heavy sedation.

135
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:43,606
I'm just trying
to make sense of this data.

136
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:46,818
Give me a couple of minutes
and I'll let you know.

137
00:09:01,124 --> 00:09:04,294
-Martha, Riley, how are you doing?
-Area 29, at the door to 28.

138
00:09:04,461 --> 00:09:07,422
-Yeah, you've got to move faster.
-We're doing our best.

139
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:12,260
"Find the next number in the sequence:
313, 331, 367."

140
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:14,554
-What?
-You said the crew knew all the answers.

141
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:16,556
The crew's changed
since we set the questions.

142
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:18,683
-You're joking.
-379.

143
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,853
-MARTHA: What?
-It's a sequence of happy primes. 379.

144
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:23,980
-Happy what?
-Just enter it.

145
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,857
Are you sure? We only get one chance.

146
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:28,234
Any number that reduces to one
when you take the sum of the square

147
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:31,071
of its digits and continue iterating
until it yields one is a happy number.

148
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:33,073
Any number that doesn't, isn't.
A happy prime is a number

149
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:35,408
that's both happy and prime.
Now type it in!

150
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:37,535
I don't know. Talk about dumbing down.

151
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,746
Don't they teach
recreational mathematics any more?

152
00:09:40,497 --> 00:09:41,831
(BEEPING)

153
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,294
-We're through!
-DOCTOR: Keep moving fast as you can.

154
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:50,465
And, Martha, be careful. There may be
something else onboard the ship.

155
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:52,759
Any time you want to unnerve me,
feel free.

156
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,094
Will do, thanks.

157
00:09:54,177 --> 00:09:56,721
COMPUTER: Impact inn 30-50.

158
00:09:57,514 --> 00:10:00,266
I can't believe our lives depend
on some stupid pub quiz.

159
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:03,978
-Is that the next one?
-Oh, this is a nightmare.

160
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:06,898
"Classical music, who had the most
pre-download number ones,

161
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,776
"Elvis Presley or The Bee-atles?"

162
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:12,695
How are we supposed to know that?

163
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:15,281
We need a backup in case they don't
reach the auxiliary engine in time.

164
00:10:15,365 --> 00:10:17,117
Come on, think.
Resources. What have we got?

165
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,868
-MARTHA: Doctor?
-What is it now?

166
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:21,454
Who had the most number ones,
Elvis or The Beatles?

167
00:10:21,538 --> 00:10:23,581
-That's pre-download.
-Elvis.

168
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:27,752
No, The Beatles! No, wait...

169
00:10:28,044 --> 00:10:30,630
Oh, what was that remix?

170
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:33,800
-I don't know. I am a bit busy.
-Fine. I'll ask someone else.

171
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:37,178
Now, where was I?
Here Comes the Sun. No, resources.

172
00:10:37,262 --> 00:10:39,055
So, the power's still working.

173
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:41,891
The generator's going.
If we can harness that... Ah!

174
00:10:41,975 --> 00:10:43,726
Use the generator to jump start the ship.

175
00:10:43,852 --> 00:10:46,896
Exactly. At the very least,
it will buy some more time.

176
00:10:47,355 --> 00:10:50,233
-That is brilliant.
-I know. See?

177
00:10:50,859 --> 00:10:53,319
-Tiny glimmer of hope.
-If it works.

178
00:10:53,403 --> 00:10:55,947
Oh, believe me,
you're gonna make it work.

179
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:00,535
That told him.

180
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:02,954
COMPUTER: Impact in 29:46.

181
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:05,832
(MOBILE RINGING)

182
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:11,379
-Hello?
-Mum, it's me. It's Martha. Wow!

183
00:11:11,462 --> 00:11:15,091
Where are you? Don't you check
your messages? I've been calling you.

184
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,135
Actually, a bit busy.
I need you to do something for me.

185
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:21,306
No, listen to me.
We have to talk about the Doctor.

186
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:23,808
Mum, please, not now! I need you
to look something up on the Internet.

187
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:27,729
-Do it yourself. You've got a computer.
-Oh, just do it, will you?

188
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:36,988
-Please.
-When did you get so rude?

189
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,700
I'll tell you when.
Ever since you met that man.

190
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:44,037
I need to know who has more
number ones, The Beatles or Elvis.

191
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,872
Hang on. The mouse is unplugged.

192
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:47,790
(GROANING)

193
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:54,214
-Okay, hang on. What is this, pub quiz?
-Yeah, pub quiz.

194
00:11:54,297 --> 00:11:57,675
-Using your mobile is cheating.
-Have you found it?

195
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:01,221
There's over 400,000 results.
Give me a minute.

196
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:04,515
COMPUTER: Impact in 28-50.

197
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:08,394
Doctor, these readings
are starting to scare me.

198
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:11,397
-What do you mean?
-Look, Korwin's body is changing.

199
00:12:11,481 --> 00:12:14,442
His whole biological make-up...
It's impossible.

200
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,860
(BEEPING)

201
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:27,830
This is med centre. Urgent assistance
requested. Urgent assistance!

202
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:30,917
Stay here! Keep working!

203
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:36,798
Urgent assistance!

204
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:39,259
Abi, they're on their way.

205
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:45,014
What's happening to you?

206
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,642
(IN ALIEN VOICE) Burn with me.

207
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:49,644
(OVER PA) Burn with me.

208
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:53,398
Captain?
I told you to stay in Engineering.

209
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:55,733
I only take orders
from one person round here.

210
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,443
Oh, is he always this cheery?

211
00:12:57,652 --> 00:12:59,195
-Elvis.
-What?

212
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:01,447
Really? Elvis!

213
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:04,117
Burn with me.

214
00:13:04,951 --> 00:13:06,577
Korwin, you're sick.

215
00:13:08,079 --> 00:13:10,999
Burn with me!

216
00:13:15,837 --> 00:13:18,840
-Mum, you're a star.
-Now, we need to have a serious...

217
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:31,019
-What was that?
-I've got to go.

218
00:13:42,697 --> 00:13:43,906
Doctor, what were those screams?

219
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:47,368
Concentrate on those doors.
You gotta keep moving forward!

220
00:13:49,037 --> 00:13:51,748
COMPUTER: Impact in 27-06.

221
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,795
Korwin's gone.

222
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:01,841
Oh, my God.

223
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:10,391
Tell me that's not Lerner.

224
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:14,937
Endothermic vaporisation.

225
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,859
I've never seen one this ferocious.

226
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:22,904
"Burn with me."

227
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:26,074
-That's what we heard Korwin say.
-What?

228
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:29,202
Do you think... No way.

229
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:32,288
Scannell, tell him.
Korwin is not a killer.

230
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:36,292
-He can't vaporise people. He's human.
-These bio-scan results.

231
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:38,878
Internal temperature, 100 degrees.

232
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,840
Body oxygen replaced by hydrogen.
Your husband hasn't been infected.

233
00:14:42,924 --> 00:14:45,635
-He's been overwhelmed.
-The test results are wrong.

234
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:48,721
What is it, though?
A parasite? A mutagenic virus?

235
00:14:48,805 --> 00:14:50,973
Something that needs a host body,
but how did it get inside him?

236
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:53,351
Stop talking
like he's some kind of experiment.

237
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:56,771
Where's this ship been?
Have you made planet fall recently?

238
00:14:56,854 --> 00:15:00,233
Docked with any other vessels?
Any sort of external contact at all?

239
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:01,776
What is this, an interrogation?

240
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,153
We've got to stop him
before he kills again.

241
00:15:04,237 --> 00:15:06,781
We're just a cargo ship.

242
00:15:09,242 --> 00:15:11,577
Doctor, if you give her a minute...

243
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:16,666
I'm fine. I need to warn the crew.

244
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:22,839
Everybody listen to me.
Something has infected Korwin.

245
00:15:24,173 --> 00:15:25,591
We think

246
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,513
he killed Abi Lerner.

247
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:36,394
None of you must go anywhere near him.
Is that clear?

248
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,605
ASHTON: Understood, Captain.

249
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:42,400
Erina, get back here
with that equipment.

250
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:46,195
Whatever you say, boss.

251
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:53,494
"Go there. Come back. Fetch this.
Carry these. Make drinks. Sweep up."”

252
00:15:54,162 --> 00:15:56,414
Please, kill me now.

253
00:15:58,583 --> 00:16:00,835
Burn with me.

254
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,548
Burn with me.

255
00:16:12,555 --> 00:16:14,891
COMPUTER: Impact inn 24-517.

256
00:16:16,017 --> 00:16:18,728
Is the infection permanent?
Can you cure him?

257
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:24,567
-I don't know.
-Don't lie to me, Doctor.

258
00:16:25,735 --> 00:16:30,448
Eleven years we've been married.
We chose this ship together.

259
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:36,078
He keeps me honest.
So I don't want false hope.

260
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:40,583
The parasite's too aggressive.
Your husband's gone.

261
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,711
There's no way back. Sorry.

262
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:48,841
Thank you.

263
00:16:51,052 --> 00:16:53,930
Are you certain
nothing happened to provoke this?

264
00:16:54,305 --> 00:16:58,226
Nobody's working on anything secret?
'Cause it's vital that you tell me.

265
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:00,853
I know every inch of this ship.

266
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:05,608
I know every detail of my crew's lives.
There is nothing.

267
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:10,112
Then why is this thing
so interested in you?

268
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:15,159
I wish I knew.

269
00:17:24,752 --> 00:17:26,754
MARTHA: Doctor, we've moved to area 17.

270
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:30,633
Keep going. You've got to get
to area 1 and reboot those engines.

271
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,802
(DOOR OPENING)

272
00:17:38,849 --> 00:17:40,851
You got those tools, Erina?
'Cause I'm...

273
00:17:40,935 --> 00:17:42,353
(EXCLAIMING)

274
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:50,778
Korwin, it's me. We're mates.

275
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:56,158
They are getting too far.
We must share the light.

276
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:14,135
COMPUTER: Heat shields failing at 20%.

277
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:16,345
Come on!

278
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,432
Everything on this ship is so cheap.

279
00:18:19,515 --> 00:18:20,600
(DOOR OPENING)

280
00:18:20,725 --> 00:18:22,184
Who's there?

281
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:33,112
MARTHA: Is that Korwin?
RILEY: No, wait a minute.

282
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,283
Oh, Ashton, what are you doing?

283
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,201
(IN ALIEN VOICE) Burn with me.

284
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:43,039
-Well, if you want to help...
-Burn with me.

285
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:46,208
Burn with me.

286
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:49,629
No! Come on!

287
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:14,070
-What is happening on this ship?
-Never mind that. Where are we?

288
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:17,990
COMPUTER:
Airlock field. Jettison escape pod.

289
00:19:18,074 --> 00:19:20,785
Does it mean us? Doctor!

290
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:23,037
COMPUTER: Pod jettison initiated.

291
00:19:24,372 --> 00:19:27,833
Doctor, we're stuck in an escape pod
of the area-17 airlock.

292
00:19:27,917 --> 00:19:31,462
One of the crew's trying to jettison us.
You've got to help us!

293
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:34,340
Tell me you can stop it.

294
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:37,760
-Why is this happening?
-Stay here.

295
00:19:37,927 --> 00:19:41,639
I mean it this time.
Don't start those engines!

296
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:54,944
He's picking us off one by one.

297
00:19:57,113 --> 00:19:58,989
COMPUTER: Jettison held.

298
00:20:00,116 --> 00:20:01,283
Thank you.

299
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:07,707
COMPUTER: Jettison reactivated.

300
00:20:10,793 --> 00:20:12,128
Come on.

301
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:23,431
Sierpinski sequence. This'll get him.

302
00:20:26,392 --> 00:20:30,271
COMPUTER:
Jettison held. Escape pod stabilised.

303
00:20:32,314 --> 00:20:33,899
You're pretty good.

304
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:42,992
Ashton!

305
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:50,750
Someone's hacked at the systems.

306
00:20:52,293 --> 00:20:54,170
I can't re-root the generators.

307
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:56,630
There's no way
I'm gonna be able to jump start the ship.

308
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:01,469
SCANNELL: Who the hell did that?

309
00:21:04,013 --> 00:21:05,681
Korwin?

310
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:12,354
What are you?
Why are you killing my crew?

311
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:18,486
What did you do to him?
What have you done to my husband?

312
00:21:20,237 --> 00:21:25,034
You recognise me. Korwin, you know me.

313
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,538
It's Kath, your wife.

314
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:32,750
-My wife?
-That's right.

315
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:37,713
You're still in there. I'm your wife.

316
00:21:41,342 --> 00:21:43,344
It's your fault.

317
00:21:56,774 --> 00:21:58,067
That's enough!

318
00:22:01,570 --> 00:22:05,157
What do you want?
Why this ship? Tell me.

319
00:22:05,241 --> 00:22:06,408
(SCREAMING)

320
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:08,327
COMPUTER: Jettison activated.

321
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:11,914
He's crushed the circuit.
I can't stop it. I can't stop it!

322
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,584
What do you mean, it's my fault?

323
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:20,256
It's your fault. Now burn with me.

324
00:22:22,508 --> 00:22:23,634
(KORWIN SHRIEKING)

325
00:22:23,717 --> 00:22:26,136
-What are you doing?
-Freezing him. Ice vents.

326
00:22:27,388 --> 00:22:28,722
You'll kill him!

327
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:33,060
Come on, let's see you.

328
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:39,233
I want to know what you really are.

329
00:22:49,702 --> 00:22:51,662
COMPUTER: Airlock sealed.

330
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:01,797
McDonnell, Ashton's heading
in your direction.

331
00:23:01,881 --> 00:23:03,757
He's been infected, just like Korwin.

332
00:23:08,012 --> 00:23:09,346
Korwin's dead, Doctor.

333
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:11,974
Everything's locked.

334
00:23:12,558 --> 00:23:15,436
COMPUTER:
Airlock decompression completed.

335
00:23:16,979 --> 00:23:18,522
Jettisoning pod.

336
00:23:18,606 --> 00:23:20,441
(BEEPING)

337
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:27,072
-Doctor!
-I'll save you.

338
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:30,951
Martha, it's too late.

339
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:33,954
-Doctor!
-I'll save you.

340
00:23:34,538 --> 00:23:36,582
I can't hear you.

341
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:38,125
(INAUDIBLE)

342
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:05,945
Sorry.

343
00:24:17,915 --> 00:24:20,376
COMPUTER: Impact in 17:05.

344
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:30,219
What did he mean, your fault?

345
00:24:33,514 --> 00:24:36,058
What are you doing?
Don't touch him. He's infected.

346
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:39,311
-We don't know how it spreads.
-You murdered him.

347
00:24:39,395 --> 00:24:41,730
-He was about to kill you.
-He recognised me.

348
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:44,984
You heard the Doctor.
It isn't Korwin any more.

349
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:47,486
The Doctor doesn't know.
None of us know.

350
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,446
So what are you gonna do?
Stay there until we burn?

351
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:53,575
'Cause without you, none of us
stand a chance of getting out of here.

352
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:56,745
DOCTOR: Scannell
I need a spacesuit in area 17 now!

353
00:24:56,829 --> 00:24:59,081
-What for?
-Just get down here!

354
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:03,752
Well, go on. Do what he says.

355
00:25:03,961 --> 00:25:07,423
-Ashton's still out there.
-I'll deal with him.

356
00:25:22,021 --> 00:25:24,273
The wonderful world of space travel.

357
00:25:25,482 --> 00:25:28,861
The prettier it looks,
the more likely it is to kill you.

358
00:25:29,069 --> 00:25:32,197
-He'll come for us.
-No, it's too late.

359
00:25:32,865 --> 00:25:36,410
Our heat shields will pack in any minute
and then we go into free fall.

360
00:25:36,952 --> 00:25:40,664
We'll fall into the sun way before
he has a chance to do anything.

361
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:45,169
You don't know the Doctor.
I believe in him.

362
00:25:46,003 --> 00:25:50,549
Then you're lucky. I've never found
anyone worth believing in.

363
00:25:53,469 --> 00:25:56,847
No girlfriend? Boyfriend?

364
00:25:57,806 --> 00:26:00,934
The job doesn't lend itself
to stable relationships.

365
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:05,355
-Family, then?
-My dad's dead.

366
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:09,777
I haven't seen my mum in six years.

367
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:13,989
She didn't want me
to sign on for cargo tours.

368
00:26:14,782 --> 00:26:19,787
Things were said,
and since then, all silent.

369
00:26:21,789 --> 00:26:25,834
She wanted to hold on to me.
I know that. God, she's so stubborn.

370
00:26:26,919 --> 00:26:28,837
Yeah, well, that's families.

371
00:26:30,964 --> 00:26:33,092
What about you?

372
00:26:33,801 --> 00:26:38,680
Full works. Mum, dad, dad's girlfriend,

373
00:26:39,556 --> 00:26:43,936
brother, sister.
There's no silence there.

374
00:26:45,646 --> 00:26:47,564
So much noise.

375
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:53,320
God, they'll never know.

376
00:26:54,238 --> 00:26:58,867
I'll just have disappeared,
and they'll always be waiting.

377
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:02,538
Call them.

378
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:08,836
Ashton!

379
00:27:39,283 --> 00:27:40,742
(GROANING)

380
00:27:50,836 --> 00:27:53,255
-I can't let you do this.
-You're wasting your breath, Scannell.

381
00:27:53,422 --> 00:27:55,507
-You're not gonna stop me.
-You want to open an airlock in flight

382
00:27:55,591 --> 00:27:57,801
on a ship spinning into the sun.
No one can survive that.

383
00:27:57,885 --> 00:28:00,304
-Oh, just you watch.
-You open that airlock, it's suicide.

384
00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:02,181
This close to the sun,
the shields will barely protect you.

385
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:04,099
If I can boost the magnetic lock
on the ship's exterior,

386
00:28:04,183 --> 00:28:06,560
it should re-magnetise the pod.
Now, while I'm out there, you've got

387
00:28:06,643 --> 00:28:09,354
to get the rest of those doors open.
We need those auxiliary engines.

388
00:28:09,438 --> 00:28:12,649
Doctor, will you listen.
They're too far away. It's too late.

389
00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:14,443
I'm not gonna lose her.

390
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:32,628
COMPUTER: Decompression initiated.

391
00:28:38,634 --> 00:28:41,094
Impact in 12:55.

392
00:28:41,637 --> 00:28:42,846
(MOBILE RINGING)

393
00:28:44,389 --> 00:28:48,185
-Hello?
-It's me again. Sorry about earlier.

394
00:28:48,268 --> 00:28:51,813
-Is everything all right?
-Yeah. Of course.

395
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:56,902
-Martha?
-Mum...

396
00:28:59,154 --> 00:29:02,950
-You know I love you, don't you?
-Of course, I do.

397
00:29:04,034 --> 00:29:06,495
-What's brought this on?
-I never say it.

398
00:29:07,663 --> 00:29:10,874
I never get the time
or never think of it, and then...

399
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,045
I really love you.

400
00:29:16,964 --> 00:29:19,675
Tell Dad, Leo and Tish
that I love them, too.

401
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:24,513
-Martha, what's wrong?
-Nothing, promise.

402
00:29:24,972 --> 00:29:27,224
-Where are you?
-Just out.

403
00:29:27,599 --> 00:29:30,727
-With anyone nice?
-Some mates.

404
00:29:30,811 --> 00:29:34,523
-What mates?
-Mum, can we not just talk?

405
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:38,735
Of course.
What do you want to talk about?

406
00:29:39,111 --> 00:29:41,321
I don't know. Anything.

407
00:29:41,405 --> 00:29:44,866
What you had for breakfast,
what you watched on telly last night,

408
00:29:45,033 --> 00:29:48,412
how much you're gonna kill Dad
next time you see him, just anything.

409
00:29:50,163 --> 00:29:53,500
Is the Doctor with you? Is he there now?

410
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:57,379
-Mum, just leave it.
-It's a simple enough question.

411
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:01,216
I better go.

412
00:30:03,885 --> 00:30:06,805
-No, Martha, wait.
-See ya, Mum.

413
00:30:22,571 --> 00:30:24,656
COMPUTER: Impact in 11:15.

414
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:24,990
Heat shields

415
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:26,366
Heat shields

416
00:30:26,742 --> 00:30:28,660
failing at 10%.

417
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:53,226
(GRUNTING)

418
00:31:04,196 --> 00:31:05,989
Come on!

419
00:31:11,536 --> 00:31:13,288
Go on, my son.

420
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:21,129
SCANNELL ON RADIO:
Doctor, how are you doing?

421
00:31:21,213 --> 00:31:24,716
I can't... I can't reach.

422
00:31:25,467 --> 00:31:27,636
I don't know how much longer I can last.

423
00:31:27,761 --> 00:31:29,721
SCANNELL: Come on, don't give up now.

424
00:32:00,168 --> 00:32:04,923
-We're being pulled back!
-I told you! The Doctor!

425
00:32:28,238 --> 00:32:30,031
It's alive.

426
00:32:32,993 --> 00:32:34,828
It's alive.

427
00:32:36,455 --> 00:32:38,123
It's alive.

428
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:42,377
Doctor, close the airlock now!
That pod's gonna smash into him.

429
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:45,046
Stay here.

430
00:32:46,298 --> 00:32:48,884
COMPUTER: Impact inn 8-5 7.

431
00:32:51,011 --> 00:32:53,680
Airlock recompression completed.

432
00:32:59,019 --> 00:33:03,106
Doctor! Doctor! Are you okay?

433
00:33:04,316 --> 00:33:06,568
(IN ALIEN VOICE) Stay away from me.

434
00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:09,488
What's happened?

435
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:12,240
It's your fault, Captain McDonnell.

436
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:16,495
Riley, get down to area 10
and help Scannell with the doors.

437
00:33:16,578 --> 00:33:17,746
Go!

438
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:21,374
You mined that sun,
stripped its surface for cheap fuel.

439
00:33:23,043 --> 00:33:25,253
-You should have scanned for life!
-I don't understand.

440
00:33:25,337 --> 00:33:27,506
Doctor, what are you talking about?

441
00:33:27,589 --> 00:33:30,258
That's sun's alive, a living organism.

442
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:35,138
They scooped out its heart, used it
for fuel and now it's screaming!

443
00:33:35,222 --> 00:33:37,933
What do you mean? How can
a sun be alive? Why is he saying that?

444
00:33:38,183 --> 00:33:40,018
Because it's living in me.

445
00:33:40,602 --> 00:33:42,312
-Oh, my God.
-Humans!

446
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:45,148
You grab whatever's nearest
and bleed it dry!

447
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:47,567
You should've scanned!

448
00:33:47,651 --> 00:33:51,655
-It takes too long. We'd be caught.
-Fusion scoops are illegal.

449
00:33:52,072 --> 00:33:53,782
Martha, you've got
to freeze me, quickly.

450
00:33:53,865 --> 00:33:56,201
-What?
-Stasis chamber.

451
00:33:57,285 --> 00:34:02,290
Look, you've got to take me
to below -200. Freeze it out of me.

452
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:07,379
It'll use me to kill you if you don't.

453
00:34:07,504 --> 00:34:10,632
The closer we get to the sun,
the stronger it is...

454
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:14,719
-Med centre. Quickly! Quickly!
-Help me!

455
00:34:17,681 --> 00:34:19,933
COMPUTER: Impact in 7-30.

456
00:34:41,621 --> 00:34:43,415
-What's your favourite colour?
-You what?

457
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:45,166
-It's the question.
-Purple.

458
00:34:48,336 --> 00:34:49,838
-Or did I say orange?
-Come on!

459
00:34:58,597 --> 00:35:01,266
-Martha, where are you?
-It's all right. I'm here.

460
00:35:01,349 --> 00:35:04,269
Just setting everything up.
Stasis chamber, minus 200, yeah?

461
00:35:04,394 --> 00:35:06,813
But you don't know how
this equipment works. You'll kill him.

462
00:35:06,896 --> 00:35:08,481
Nobody can survive those temperatures.

463
00:35:08,565 --> 00:35:10,525
He's not human.
If he says he can survive, then he can.

464
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:13,528
-Let me help you, then.
-You've done enough damage.

465
00:35:15,363 --> 00:35:18,074
Ten seconds.
That's all I'll be able to take.

466
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:20,702
-Martha!
-Yeah?

467
00:35:21,828 --> 00:35:24,289
It's burning me up. I can't control it.

468
00:35:24,539 --> 00:35:28,877
If you don't get rid of it,
I could kill you. I could kill you all.

469
00:35:30,712 --> 00:35:34,633
-I'm scared. I'm so scared.
-Just stay calm.

470
00:35:35,008 --> 00:35:39,512
You saved me. Now I return the favour.
Just believe in me.

471
00:35:39,596 --> 00:35:41,723
It's burning. Kill me.
Then it won't happen.

472
00:35:42,891 --> 00:35:44,976
That's enough. I've got you.

473
00:35:45,101 --> 00:35:49,981
There's this process...this thing
that happens if I'm about to die...

474
00:35:50,065 --> 00:35:53,485
Shh! Quiet now,
'cause that is not going to happen.

475
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:55,945
-You ready?
-No.

476
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:21,221
COMPUTER: Heat shields failing at 5%.

477
00:36:46,079 --> 00:36:48,915
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

478
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:53,128
No! Martha, you can't stop it! Not yet!

479
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:56,256
-What happened?
-The power's been cut in Engineering.

480
00:36:57,215 --> 00:37:00,760
-But who's down there?
-Leave it to me.

481
00:37:03,555 --> 00:37:05,265
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

482
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:09,644
COMPUTER: Impact in 4:47.

483
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:19,028
Are we gonna do it in time?

484
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,454
Come on, you're defrosting.

485
00:37:27,996 --> 00:37:31,082
Martha, listen, I could go
at any moment. You've got to go.

486
00:37:31,166 --> 00:37:34,711
-No way.
-Get to the front. Vent the engines.

487
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:37,589
Sun particles in the fuel.
Get rid of them.

488
00:37:37,672 --> 00:37:40,008
-I am not leaving you.
-You've got to!

489
00:37:41,259 --> 00:37:43,136
Give back what they took.

490
00:37:43,219 --> 00:37:45,680
-Doctor.
-Please, go!

491
00:37:46,389 --> 00:37:48,016
I'll be back for you.

492
00:37:48,183 --> 00:37:50,226
COMPUTER: Impact inn 4-08.

493
00:37:54,314 --> 00:37:55,440
(GASPING)

494
00:37:58,860 --> 00:38:03,490
You were right. It was my fault.

495
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:16,461
COMPUTER: Impact in 3:43.

496
00:38:57,919 --> 00:39:01,756
I didn't know. I really didn't know.

497
00:39:02,215 --> 00:39:03,967
Korwin, please stop.

498
00:39:06,052 --> 00:39:09,097
Everyone must burn.

499
00:39:12,642 --> 00:39:16,104
Riley, Scannell, I'm sorry.

500
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,314
McDonnell! McDonnell!

501
00:39:21,109 --> 00:39:22,944
I love you.

502
00:39:34,289 --> 00:39:36,666
COMPUTER: Exterior airlock opened.

503
00:39:37,417 --> 00:39:39,794
It's the last door.
We've got to keep going.

504
00:39:44,340 --> 00:39:46,801
COMPUTER: Impact in 2:17.

505
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:56,603
Primary engine critical.
Repeat, primary engine critical.

506
00:40:10,742 --> 00:40:14,120
Survival estimate projection, 0%.

507
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:21,753
Martha!

508
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:27,050
Doctor! What are you doing?

509
00:40:28,843 --> 00:40:30,053
I can't fight it.

510
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:33,181
(OVER PA) Keep back, Martha!

511
00:40:37,393 --> 00:40:38,519
Burn with me.

512
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:41,439
(OVER PA) Burn with me, Martha.

513
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:44,192
COMPUTER: Impact in 1:21.

514
00:40:48,571 --> 00:40:49,864
Got it!

515
00:40:50,531 --> 00:40:53,117
COMPUTER:
Life support systems reaching critical.

516
00:40:53,201 --> 00:40:56,496
Repeat, life support systems
reaching critical.

517
00:40:57,622 --> 00:40:59,832
Impact inn 7-06.

518
00:40:59,916 --> 00:41:01,000
(ALARM BLARING)

519
00:41:01,084 --> 00:41:03,586
Collision alert. Collision alert.

520
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:05,880
It's not working. Why is it not working?

521
00:41:05,964 --> 00:41:09,467
COMPUTER: Collision alert.
Fifty eight seconds to fatal impact.

522
00:41:09,550 --> 00:41:13,054
-Vent the engines. Dump the fuel.
-What?

523
00:41:13,137 --> 00:41:18,267
Sun particles in the fuel.
Get rid of them. Do it. Now!

524
00:41:24,273 --> 00:41:26,067
Come on, Doctor, hold on.

525
00:41:28,653 --> 00:41:33,074
COMPUTER: Fuel dump in progress.
Fuel dump in progress.

526
00:41:55,263 --> 00:41:58,099
Ah, the engines are firing!

527
00:42:09,777 --> 00:42:15,283
COMPUTER: Impact averted.
Impact averted. Impact averted.

528
00:42:20,621 --> 00:42:22,457
We're clear.

529
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:26,753
We've got just enough reserves.

530
00:42:31,466 --> 00:42:33,342
Doctor!

531
00:42:56,324 --> 00:42:59,285
-This is never your ship.
-Compact, eh?

532
00:42:59,827 --> 00:43:04,916
And another good word, robust.
Barely a scorch mark on her.

533
00:43:05,166 --> 00:43:07,085
We can't just leave you
drifting with no fuel.

534
00:43:07,251 --> 00:43:09,045
We've sent out an official mayday.

535
00:43:09,170 --> 00:43:10,922
The authorities
will pick us up soon enough.

536
00:43:11,005 --> 00:43:14,175
-Though how we explain what happened...
-Just tell them.

537
00:43:14,258 --> 00:43:17,637
That sun needs care and protection,
just like any other living thing.

538
00:43:19,847 --> 00:43:23,935
So you're off, then.

539
00:43:25,478 --> 00:43:29,899
-No chance I'll see you again?
-Not really.

540
00:43:30,942 --> 00:43:34,529
It was nice, not dying with you.

541
00:43:37,740 --> 00:43:40,618
I reckon you'll find
someone worth believing in.

542
00:43:41,369 --> 00:43:43,371
I think I already did.

543
00:43:58,344 --> 00:44:02,056
Well done. Very hot.

544
00:44:05,101 --> 00:44:08,396
So, didn't really need you
in the end, did we?

545
00:44:11,357 --> 00:44:12,692
Sorry.

546
00:44:14,569 --> 00:44:16,070
How are you doing?

547
00:44:17,405 --> 00:44:18,990
Now, what do you say?

548
00:44:19,073 --> 00:44:21,993
Ice-skating on the mineral lakes
of Kur-ha. Fancy it?

549
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:23,870
Whatever you like.

550
00:44:26,998 --> 00:44:30,418
By the way, you'll be needing this.

551
00:44:32,628 --> 00:44:34,839
-Really?
-Frequent flyers' privilege.

552
00:44:41,971 --> 00:44:45,725
-Thank you.
-Don't mention it.

553
00:44:47,768 --> 00:44:50,730
Oh, no! Mum!

554
00:44:55,276 --> 00:44:56,694
(MOBILE RINGING)

555
00:44:57,528 --> 00:44:58,613
Hello?

556
00:44:58,946 --> 00:45:01,449
-It's me again.
-Three calls in one day.

557
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:04,619
I'm sorry about earlier.
Over-emotional mad day.

558
00:45:04,744 --> 00:45:06,954
What are you doing tonight?
Why don't you come round?

559
00:45:07,038 --> 00:45:09,123
I'll make something nice
and we can catch up.

560
00:45:09,874 --> 00:45:13,127
Yeah, tonight. Do my best.

561
00:45:13,419 --> 00:45:15,504
Just remind me, what day is it again?

562
00:45:15,630 --> 00:45:18,257
-Election day.
-Right. Of course.

563
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:20,593
I'll be round for tea, roughly.

564
00:45:20,718 --> 00:45:22,595
-And what about...
-Anyway, I've got to go.

565
00:45:22,678 --> 00:45:24,722
See you later. Love you.

566
00:45:38,236 --> 00:45:40,363
-That's all?
-For now.

567
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:42,782
-Have you voted?
-Of course.

568
00:45:43,324 --> 00:45:45,701
Just don't expect me
to tell you who for.

569
00:45:45,785 --> 00:45:50,289
Thanks for all you're doing, Mrs Jones.
Mr Saxon will be very grateful.

570
00:45:57,713 --> 00:45:59,674
Martha, this watch is...

571
00:46:01,175 --> 00:46:03,511
If anything goes wrong,
it's all down to you, Martha.

572
00:46:05,263 --> 00:46:07,556
It's Monday, November 10, 1913.

573
00:46:08,849 --> 00:46:11,143
-We make quite a team.
-Don't we just.

574
00:46:11,227 --> 00:46:12,728
You've quite an eye for a pretty girl.

575
00:46:12,812 --> 00:46:13,854
Look in the sky.

576
00:46:14,021 --> 00:46:15,273
Help me!

577
00:46:23,823 --> 00:46:27,493
"Completely human”. Hmm.

